						               													<description>There is something magical about the ice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Components:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3 glacier tiles&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Set-up:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Use 1 more Land Tile than is required for the number of players. Place the 3 Glacier tiles in any 3 different terrains on the board with either side face-up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a battleground contains a Glacier, gain plus 1 power to attack or defend for each creature whose heraldry symbol matches that Glacier tile. If, after you were successful in a battle (attack or defense), either player used a matching heraldry symbol for the Glacier space, you may move the Glacier tile to an uncontrolled terrain with either side of the tile facing up. If there are no spaces available remove the Glacier Tile&amp;#10;&amp;#10;No control cubes may be placed on a landscape with a Glacier tile. The land is considered controlled as long as the hero remains on that space. Control Cubes may be placed on the landscape immediately after the Glacier has been moved. The controlling hero cannot be substituted for instances where control cubes need to be removed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
